```

---

# 18.6 Add Environment Variables

Go to:

```plaintext id="j7txcf"
Environment → Add Environment Variables
```

Add all database variables:

```env id="if2jlwm"
db_host=your_host
db_user=your_username
db_password=your_password
db_database=your_database
db_port=3306
```

---

# 18.7 Deploy Application

Click:

```plaintext id="w94jlwm"
Create Web Service
```

Render automatically:

* Installs dependencies
* Builds application
* Starts FastAPI server
* Generates public API URL

---

# 18.8 Deployment URL

After successful deployment, Render provides a public URL such as:

```plaintext id="q1jlwm"
https://expense-tracker-backend.onrender.com
```

Example API:

```plaintext id="jlwmz4"
https://expense-tracker-backend.onrender.com/docs
```


# 18.9 Common Deployment Errors

| Error                  | Reason                  | Solution                        |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| ModuleNotFoundError    | Missing package         | Add package to requirements.txt |
| MySQL Connection Error | Invalid DB credentials  | Verify environment variables    |
| App Crash              | Syntax/runtime error    | Check Render logs               |
| Port Binding Error     | Incorrect start command | Use Render port configuration   |
| CORS Error             | Frontend origin blocked | Verify CORS settings            |

---

# 18.10 Updating the Backend

To update deployed backend:

1. Modify backend code locally
2. Push changes to GitHub
3. Render automatically redeploys application

---

# 18.11 Benefits of Using Render

Advantages:

* Free hosting tier
* Easy GitHub integration
* Automatic deployments
* Environment variable support
* Live logs and monitoring
* HTTPS enabled by default

---

# 18.12 Frontend-Backend Integration

The frontend Streamlit application communicates with the deployed Render backend using:

```python id="y0g9kz"
server = st.secrets["be_server_url"]
```

Example:

```toml id="jlwm8f"
be_server_url = "https://expense-tracker-backend.onrender.com"
```

This enables secure API communication between frontend and backend applications.

